{
  "text": "Soluble type II TGF-\uf062 receptor, which binds TGF-\uf0621 and TGF-\uf0623, was implemented in three MM mouse models. The AB12 and AC29 models produce large amounts of TGF-\uf062, while the AB1 model does not. Predictably, suppression of tumour growth attributed to the addition of the soluble TGF-\uf062 receptor was only evident in the AB12 and AC29 tumours. CD8 + T cells were responsible for tumour cell killing following treatment, but were less efficient in bulky TGF-\uf062 secreting tumours. Furthermore, complete regressions were not observed [CITATION_1] .",
